  "texts": [
    "The CBA achieved exceptional selectivity exceeding 10 10 with the aid of selective devices.Transistors are fundamental components with three terminals, while memristors are commonly integrated above the source/drain bias of the underlying transistor.",
    "In a 1T1R structure, device selection is achieved by gate voltage at the WLs.",
    "Applying varying gate voltages to different WLs allows for low current in unselected devices where the transistor remains off [122,123].",
    "Furthermore, the devices at the selected WL are further controlled by the BL voltage, which is applied across the channel of the transistor and the memristor.",
    "demonstrated a CMOS-based 1T1R crossbar array using h-BN, achieving high endurance and excellent switching uniformity by leveraging the precise compliance current control of the transistor."
  ],
